# "Burst makes sure that the actual output rate is limited to the maximum the
# DROID hardware can do, so not one single burst can get lost." At a very high
# hz the requested period is far below one tick; the hardware limits the rate so
# every one of the `count` pulses is still emitted.
#
# SPEC-GAP: the manual gives no exact maximum output rate. We clamp the period
# to a minimum of 2 ticks (1 tick high + 1 tick low = max rate tickRate/2), which
# guarantees no pulse is dropped. Hardware reference data on the true maximum
# would close this gap. Here hz=100 at tickrate 8 requests P=0.08 ticks; clamped
# to P=2. count=3 -> pulses at k=0,2,4 (each 1 tick high, 1 low), none lost.
#   trigger t1: HIGH at t1,t3,t5; LOW between; done after 3 pulses.
tickrate 8
patch <<<
[burst]
    trigger = I1
    hz      = 100
    count   = 3
    output  = O1
>>>
@0 expect O1 0
@1 set I1 1
@1 expect O1 1
@2 set I1 0
@2 expect O1 0
@3 expect O1 1
@4 expect O1 0
@5 expect O1 1
@6 expect O1 0
@7 expect O1 0
@8 expect O1 0
